added Task class

Added Event class

Added DukeException class

Added Storage class. Organized methods and variables that deal with loading and saving into Storage class.
Added TaskList class. Organized methods that involve operations on tasks into TaskList.
Add Ui class
commitResults.messageBody:
Enums are clogging up space in Duke.

As commands and other recognized inputs by Duke chatbot increases later, it can get increasingly difficult to navigate around and manage code.

Enums are extracted to Ui class.

Change to have Duke constructor initialize storage and tasklist objects

Storage class methods are static and Duke does not have a constructor.
Multiple methods are being called in main method, which is bad for code readability.
Filename is kept as a static constant in Storage class and can be difficult for developers to find later on.

Abstract Storage and Tasklist initializations away to Duke class constructor.
Move scanning for and handling user inputs into run method in Duke class.
Move Filename for save file to Duke where main method is at.

Developers set up Duke chatbot by just creating a Duke object and can run it by calling run method.
Developers can easily see the filename for the save file in Duke class.

commitResults.messageBody:
No Storable interface.

Unable to create Stub for Storage class.

Add Storable interface and have StorageStub and Storage class implement it.

StorageStub class can be created for unit testing purposes.

Add JUnit5 tests for AddCommand and introduced new exception messages

Exception messages do not check for missing spaces in user input.

Added new checks and appropriate exception messages.

This is so user can better understand why their input is invalid.
